#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/testing/mockmvc/htmlunit/why.adoc:8
msgid ""
"The most obvious question that comes to mind is \"`Why do I need this?`\" "
"The answer is best found by exploring a very basic sample "
"application. Assume you have a Spring MVC web application that supports CRUD "
"operations on a `Message` object. The application also supports paging "
"through all messages. How would you go about testing it?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/testing/mockmvc/htmlunit/why.adoc:10
msgid ""
"With Spring MVC Test, we can easily test if we are able to create a "
"`Message`, as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/testing/mockmvc/htmlunit/why.adoc:13
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/testing/mockmvc/htmlunit/why.adoc:68
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/testing/mockmvc/htmlunit/why.adoc:95
#, no-wrap
msgid "Java"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/testing/mockmvc/htmlunit/why.adoc:20
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tMockHttpServletRequestBuilder createMessage = post(\"/messages/\")\n"
"\t\t\t.param(\"summary\", \"Spring Rocks\")\n"
"\t\t\t.param(\"text\", \"In case you didn't know, Spring Rocks!\");\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/testing/mockmvc/htmlunit/why.adoc:24
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/testing/mockmvc/htmlunit/why.adoc:113
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tmockMvc.perform(createMessage)\n"
"\t\t\t.andExpect(status().is3xxRedirection())\n"
"\t\t\t.andExpect(redirectedUrl(\"/messages/123\"));\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/testing/mockmvc/htmlunit/why.adoc:26
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/testing/mockmvc/htmlunit/why.adoc:77
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/testing/mockmvc/htmlunit/why.adoc:115
#, no-wrap
msgid "Kotlin"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/testing/mockmvc/htmlunit/why.adoc:40
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\t@Test\n"
"\tfun test() {\n"
"\t\tmockMvc.post(\"/messages/\") {\n"
"\t\t\tparam(\"summary\", \"Spring Rocks\")\n"
"\t\t\tparam(\"text\", \"In case you didn't know, Spring Rocks!\")\n"
"\t\t}.andExpect {\n"
"\t\t\tstatus().is3xxRedirection()\n"
"\t\t\tredirectedUrl(\"/messages/123\")\n"
"\t\t}\n"
"\t}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/testing/mockmvc/htmlunit/why.adoc:45
msgid ""
"What if we want to test the form view that lets us create the message? For "
"example, assume our form looks like the following snippet:"
msgstr ""

