#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/testing/mockmvc/htmlunit/why.adoc:50
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\t<form id=\"messageForm\" action=\"/messages/\" method=\"post\">\n"
"\t\t<div class=\"pull-right\"><a href=\"/messages/\">Messages</a></div>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/testing/mockmvc/htmlunit/why.adoc:53
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\t\t<label for=\"summary\">Summary</label>\n"
"\t\t<input type=\"text\" class=\"required\" id=\"summary\" name=\"summary\" "
"value=\"\" />\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/testing/mockmvc/htmlunit/why.adoc:56
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\t\t<label for=\"text\">Message</label>\n"
"\t\t<textarea id=\"text\" name=\"text\"></textarea>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/testing/mockmvc/htmlunit/why.adoc:61
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\t\t<div class=\"form-actions\">\n"
"\t\t\t<input type=\"submit\" value=\"Create\" />\n"
"\t\t</div>\n"
"\t</form>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/testing/mockmvc/htmlunit/why.adoc:65
msgid ""
"How do we ensure that our form produces the correct request to create a new "
"message? A naive attempt might resemble the following:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/testing/mockmvc/htmlunit/why.adoc:75
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tmockMvc.perform(get(\"/messages/form\"))\n"
"\t\t\t.andExpect(xpath(\"//input[@name='summary']\").exists())\n"
"\t\t\t.andExpect(xpath(\"//textarea[@name='text']\").exists());\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/testing/mockmvc/htmlunit/why.adoc:85
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tmockMvc.get(\"/messages/form\").andExpect {\n"
"\t\txpath(\"//input[@name='summary']\") { exists() }\n"
"\t\txpath(\"//textarea[@name='text']\") { exists() }\n"
"\t}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/testing/mockmvc/htmlunit/why.adoc:92
msgid ""
"This test has some obvious drawbacks. If we update our controller to use the "
"parameter `message` instead of `text`, our form test continues to pass, even "
"though the HTML form is out of sync with the controller. To resolve this we "
"can combine our two tests, as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/testing/mockmvc/htmlunit/why.adoc:105
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tString summaryParamName = \"summary\";\n"
"\tString textParamName = \"text\";\n"
"\tmockMvc.perform(get(\"/messages/form\"))\n"
"\t\t\t.andExpect(xpath(\"//input[@name='\" + summaryParamName + "
"\"']\").exists())\n"
"\t\t\t.andExpect(xpath(\"//textarea[@name='\" + textParamName + "
"\"']\").exists());\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/testing/mockmvc/htmlunit/why.adoc:109
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tMockHttpServletRequestBuilder createMessage = post(\"/messages/\")\n"
"\t\t\t.param(summaryParamName, \"Spring Rocks\")\n"
"\t\t\t.param(textParamName, \"In case you didn't know, Spring Rocks!\");\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/testing/mockmvc/htmlunit/why.adoc:132
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tval summaryParamName = \"summary\";\n"
"\tval textParamName = \"text\";\n"
"\tmockMvc.get(\"/messages/form\").andExpect {\n"
"\t\txpath(\"//input[@name='$summaryParamName']\") { exists() }\n"
"\t\txpath(\"//textarea[@name='$textParamName']\") { exists() }\n"
"\t}\n"
"\tmockMvc.post(\"/messages/\") {\n"
"\t\tparam(summaryParamName, \"Spring Rocks\")\n"
"\t\tparam(textParamName, \"In case you didn't know, Spring Rocks!\")\n"
"\t}.andExpect {\n"
"\t\tstatus().is3xxRedirection()\n"
"\t\tredirectedUrl(\"/messages/123\")\n"
"\t}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/testing/mockmvc/htmlunit/why.adoc:137
msgid ""
"This would reduce the risk of our test incorrectly passing, but there are "
"still some problems:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/testing/mockmvc/htmlunit/why.adoc:141
msgid ""
"What if we have multiple forms on our page? Admittedly, we could update our "
"XPath expressions, but they get more complicated as we take more factors "
"into account: Are the fields the correct type? Are the fields enabled? And "
"so on."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/testing/mockmvc/htmlunit/why.adoc:144
msgid ""
"Another issue is that we are doing double the work we would expect. We must "
"first verify the view, and then we submit the view with the same parameters "
"we just verified.  Ideally, this could be done all at once."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/testing/mockmvc/htmlunit/why.adoc:146
msgid ""
"Finally, we still cannot account for some things. For example, what if the "
"form has JavaScript validation that we wish to test as well?"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/testing/mockmvc/htmlunit/why.adoc:153
msgid ""
"The overall problem is that testing a web page does not involve a single "
"interaction.  Instead, it is a combination of how the user interacts with a "
"web page and how that web page interacts with other resources. For example, "
"the result of a form view is used as the input to a user for creating a "
"message. In addition, our form view can potentially use additional resources "
"that impact the behavior of the page, such as JavaScript validation."
msgstr ""

